@startuml
title Gapfish Deployer - Deployment Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "depctl CLI" as CLI
participant "DeployServerCreator" as Server
participant "EventStreamLogger" as EventLogger
participant "Configuration\nManager" as Config
participant "Git" as Git
participant "Resource\nModifier" as ResourceMod
participant "kubectl" as Kubectl
participant "Kubernetes\nCluster" as K8s
participant "Plugin\n(Bugsnag)" as Plugin

User -> CLI: depctl deploy <repository> <tag>
activate CLI

CLI -> Server: POST /deploy
activate Server

Server -> EventLogger: Initialize deployment event
activate EventLogger
EventLogger -> Plugin: Notify deployment started
activate Plugin
Plugin --> EventLogger: ACK
deactivate Plugin
EventLogger --> Server: Event logged
deactivate EventLogger

Server -> Config: Load config.yml
activate Config
Config -> Config: Parse YAML configuration
Config -> Config: Load environment variables
Config --> Server: Repository configuration
deactivate Config

Server -> Git: Clone/Pull repository
activate Git
Git -> Git: Fetch specific commit/tag
Git --> Server: Repository ready
deactivate Git

Server -> Config: Load Kubernetes resource definitions
activate Config
Config -> Config: Read Deployment YAML
Config -> Config: Read Service YAML
Config --> Server: Resource templates
deactivate Config

Server -> ResourceMod: Modify resources with image tag
activate ResourceMod
ResourceMod -> ResourceMod: Update image tag
ResourceMod -> ResourceMod: Inject ConfigMaps/Secrets
ResourceMod -> ResourceMod: Apply environment variables
ResourceMod --> Server: Modified resource definitions
deactivate ResourceMod

Server -> EventLogger: Log resource preparation complete
activate EventLogger
EventLogger --> Server: ACK
deactivate EventLogger

Server -> Kubectl: kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml
activate Kubectl
Kubectl -> K8s: Create/Update Deployment
activate K8s
K8s --> Kubectl: Deployment created/updated
deactivate K8s
Kubectl --> Server: Success
deactivate Kubectl

Server -> Kubectl: kubectl apply -f service.yaml
activate Kubectl
Kubectl -> K8s: Create/Update Service
activate K8s
K8s --> Kubectl: Service created/updated
deactivate K8s
Kubectl --> Server: Success
deactivate Kubectl

Server -> EventLogger: Log deployment success
activate EventLogger
EventLogger -> Plugin: Notify deployment completed
activate Plugin
Plugin --> EventLogger: ACK
deactivate Plugin
EventLogger --> Server: Event logged
deactivate EventLogger

Server --> CLI: Deployment successful
deactivate Server

CLI --> User: Display deployment status
deactivate CLI

== Canary Deployment Flow ==

User -> CLI: depctl canary <repository> <tag>
activate CLI

CLI -> Server: POST /canary
activate Server

Server -> EventLogger: Initialize canary deployment
activate EventLogger
EventLogger --> Server: Event logged
deactivate EventLogger

Server -> Config: Load configuration
activate Config
Config --> Server: Configuration loaded
deactivate Config

Server -> Git: Fetch canary version
activate Git
Git --> Server: Repository ready
deactivate Git

Server -> ResourceMod: Modify resources for canary
activate ResourceMod
ResourceMod -> ResourceMod: Set canary image tag
ResourceMod -> ResourceMod: Configure canary routing
ResourceMod --> Server: Canary resources ready
deactivate ResourceMod

Server -> Kubectl: kubectl apply -f canary-deployment.yaml
activate Kubectl
Kubectl -> K8s: Create canary deployment
activate K8s
K8s --> Kubectl: Canary deployed
deactivate K8s
Kubectl --> Server: Success
deactivate Kubectl

Server -> EventLogger: Log canary deployment complete
activate EventLogger
EventLogger -> Plugin: Notify canary status
activate Plugin
Plugin --> EventLogger: ACK
deactivate Plugin
EventLogger --> Server: Event logged
deactivate EventLogger

Server --> CLI: Canary deployment successful
deactivate Server

CLI --> User: Display canary status
deactivate CLI

== Status Check Flow ==

User -> CLI: depctl status <repository>
activate CLI

CLI -> Server: GET /status/<repository>
activate Server

Server -> Kubectl: kubectl get deployments
activate Kubectl
Kubectl -> K8s: Query deployment status
activate K8s
K8s --> Kubectl: Deployment status
deactivate K8s
Kubectl --> Server: Status information
deactivate Kubectl

Server --> CLI: Return status
deactivate Server

CLI --> User: Display status
deactivate CLI

@enduml
